text: Daniela Samulski (31 May 1984 – 22 May 2018) was a German swimmer. She was born in Berlin. She won three medals at the 2009 World Championships. She competed at the 2000 and 2008 Olympics in five events in total, with the best achievement of fourth place in the 4 × 100 m freestyle relay in 2000.Daniela Samulski . sports-reference.com Samulski retired in early 2011.Daniela Samulski Retires from Swimming . Swimming World Magazine. 14 January 2011 Samulski died of stomach cancer in Berlin on 22 May 2018 at the age of 33. ==References== Category:1984 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from stomach cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Germany Category:Olympians for Germany Category:German swimmers Category:Sportspeople from Berlin
